00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,280
 of weapons, of all kinds of stuff going on.

334
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:14,100
 So they could get the money that they got last year, this year.

335
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:16,600
 Because if you don't spend it, you don't get it, right?

336
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:20,460
 So it's like this, spending down, spending up, spending down, spending up.

337
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,060
 And now it's a slow, it's a lull.

338
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:23,520
 There won't be much happening right now.

339
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,920
 But it's starting in January.

340
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:27,820
 It's going to start busting up again.

341
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:29,000
 And who knows what they're going to do with that.

342
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,480
 But it's just, God, you know, the Middle East.

343
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:32,940
 And then we have, you know, seven wars.

344
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:39,480
 And none of them are truly for anything that's real.

345
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:43,720
 And excuse me, even if people say, well, Putin did invade.

346
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:46,240
 Well, he warned 14 years, 15 years, 16 years.

347
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,120
 He warned, stop, stop, stop, stop, stop.

348
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:51,460
 And he kept, they kept coming on and coming on.

349
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:52,620
 And they pushed it hard.

350
00:19:52,620 --> 00:19:54,440
 You know, they have the Victoria Newland.

351
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:57,540
 I mean, all these people that just push, push, push, push, push until he did what they

352
00:19:57,540 --> 00:19:58,180
 wanted him to do.

353
00:19:58,180 --> 00:20:00,520
 And they said, aha, look, look what he's doing.

354
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,160
 He's a bad guy.

355
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,100
 So it's all, it's all a joke.

356
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:04,860
 I'm tired of it.

357
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:11,040
 I'm really concerned that the world has become so normalized that people just go about their

358
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:16,960
 day and don't even realize that we're crumbling where we stand as sovereign nations.

359
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:24,760
 Does it bother you when people say how many wars your country has started and how it has

360
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:28,260
 introduced democracy far away from America?

361
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:35,280
 Yeah, I get, I get, I get trouble all the time from Americans when I talk about this

362
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:42,480
 because sure, you know, when, when I went into Kuwait back in 1991, I was there to, to free

363
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:45,180
 them from Saddam and to bring them democracy.

364
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:47,620
 And in the case of Kuwait, it's a great country.

365
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:48,280
 It's safe.

366
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,440
 There's no wars there now.

367
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:50,200
 It's, it's, it's great.

368
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:53,280
 Of course, it's occupied basically by the United States.

369
00:20:53,280 --> 00:21:01,360
 Um, so in my mind at that time, I was like, okay, we did our job, but Libya, Syria, Afghanistan,

370
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:04,160
 and the list goes on and on and on.

371
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:08,320
 Uh, it's worse than it was when we went in and before we went in.

372
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:13,660
 And it's just, if you can't face that because you're patriotic, or if you can't say that because

373
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:16,800
 you're scared, you're going to lose your job, or you're going to get labeled a hater or a

374
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:22,340
 leftist or a rightist or whatever, then you should question your, your, your, um, integrity on this.

375
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,720
 For me, it's real simple.

376
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,400
 I get it.

377
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:31,880
 When a father who works in Raytheon at the defense department, you know, and he's making $250,000

378
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:35,640
 a year, he's got a mortgage for, you know, for a big house for his family.

379
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:36,920
 And he's got kids in college.

380
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:42,520
 He can't afford to speak out because if he does or loses job, he loses everything.

381
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,320
 But still, that's not an excuse for me.

382
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,320
 That's why I speak out.

383
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:51,560
 If I lose everything, which I've lost, I was, I was homeless in 2008 in Berlin, Germany.

384
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,200
 I didn't have a home.

385
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:52,680
 I didn't have money.

386
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:55,320
 I lost everything overnight gone, right?

387
00:21:55,320 --> 00:22:00,040
 Lived in my car in a smart, smart car.

388
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:04,200
 I'm six, I'm 193, 204, I'm 118 kilos.

389
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:09,880
 So you can imagine me living in a smart car, but you know, and so, so I know what it's like

390
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,320
 to lose everything, but you know what?

391
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:16,200
 It was true freedom for me because I realized right then, the only reason I didn't move and

392
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:20,040
 do what I wanted to do in my life is because I thought I had to do this, this, and that to keep

393
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:24,200
 this sacred and to pay for that and to make sure this happens and this, none of it.

394
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:29,160
 If we allow ourselves to be programmed by the society around us as saying that you must be

395
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:35,480
 obedient or you're going to lose everything, we will lose much more than our house and our car

396
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,880
 and on whatever it is that we're going to lose much more.

397
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:41,000
 Let's talk about the USA today.

398
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,680
 How is life in America today?

399
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:49,960
 You know, um, besides the narrative, look, it's, it's left and right are this big.

400
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,800
 They get all the attention.

401
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,320
 Real America is right here.

402
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:55,000
 Okay.

403
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:59,160
 I have friends that are farther left, farther right, in the middle, and all of us say the

404
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:01,080
 same thing to me, Stephen, keep going.

405
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:05,720
 Your, your message of unity is so we, I was in Italy, like I said, and I met these two people,

406
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:07,080
 and they were ultra liberal.

407
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:07,880
 That's what they looked like.

408
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:10,760
 Outro little horn of glasses and the whole works and a little, you know,

409
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:13,000
 and they just looked ultimately talk liberal, they act liberal.

410
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,680
 And they said, no, we're actually centrists.

411
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:18,040
 And what you're talking about is what we need.

412
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:19,320
 We need a centrist party.

413
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:21,880
 I said, well, a centrist party will get, you know, demolished.

414
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:22,520
 It will never win.

415
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:28,040
 And more and more people are waking up and saying, wait, I don't care about the far right.

416
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:32,280
 And I don't care about the far left because that's just labels and press and propaganda.

417
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:34,600
 This is America right here.

418
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:38,360
 So living in America is still, it's still a great place to live.

419
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,240
 It's still the land of, um, unparalleled opportunity.

420
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,120
 It really is.

421
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:46,840
 And if I look around, the one thing that happened, that was the main thing when I traveled around

422
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:51,400
 Europe and I lived in 10 countries was my attitude towards business, towards work,

423
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:55,000
 towards contacts, towards building a, uh, you know, building a, uh, a network.

